<subSubSection id="20EB21ED3D096226FF2AFB24FDD34DD0" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="684E72663D096226FF2AFB24FDD34DD0" blockId="1.[151,1437,1084,2009]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">
<emphasis id="5A85AE743D096226FF2AFB24FEE84DA8" bold="true" box="[199,314,1156,1181]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="AFF109E53D096226FEAAFB24FD924DA9" box="[327,576,1156,1180]" class="Insecta" family="Hemerobiidae" genus="Hemerobiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="periotoi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="5A85AE743D096226FEAAFB24FD924DA9" box="[327,576,1156,1180]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">Hemerobiella periotoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="41B6130F3D096226FDABFB24FD4C4DA9" box="[582,670,1156,1181]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" rank="species">
<emphasis id="5A85AE743D096226FDABFB24FDB24DA8" bold="true" box="[582,608,1156,1181]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">sp</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="5A85AE743D096226FD83FB24FD4A4DA8" bold="true" box="[622,664,1156,1181]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is the only known species in the genus with a circular black mark on the second and third radial sector in the forewing (
<figureCitation id="F0CA6EE33D096226FD2AFB07FCD74DF5" box="[711,773,1191,1216]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1553,1575]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,198,1515]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,193,1516]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hemerobiella periotoi Sosa &amp; Lara sp. nov. female (Rio Claro “ Piedra del Tigre sector ” Lara state, Venezuela). A. Habitus. B. Head, frontal. C. Head and thorax, dorsal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/253673/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">
Fig. 
<number id="DE3960413D096226FD16FB08FCD74DF5" box="[763,773,1192,1216]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A) and the only one in which the ninth tergite of the female is without an anteroventral lobe.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="20EB21ED3D096226FF2AFB4FFB404EEC" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" type="description">
<paragraph id="684E72663D096226FF2AFB4FFA4E4C40" blockId="1.[151,1437,1084,2009]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">
<emphasis id="5A85AE743D096226FF2AFB4FFE834C3D" bold="true" box="[199,337,1263,1288]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">Description</emphasis>
. Head (
<figureCitation id="F0CA6EE33D096226FE41FB4FFE3E4C3D" box="[428,492,1263,1288]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1553,1575]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,198,1515]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,193,1516]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hemerobiella periotoi Sosa &amp; Lara sp. nov. female (Rio Claro “ Piedra del Tigre sector ” Lara state, Venezuela). A. Habitus. B. Head, frontal. C. Head and thorax, dorsal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/253673/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">
Fig. 
<number id="DE3960413D096226FE0CFB50FE3E4C3D" box="[481,492,1264,1288]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
B) light brown, 
<number id="DE3960413D096226FD48FB50FD1A4C3D" box="[677,712,1264,1288]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" value="1.1">1.1</number>
times as high as wide; vertex raised posteriorly, marked brown, densely covered by dark and light brown pilosity; frons slightly raised medially, bearing sparse light brown pilosity; maxillary and labial palpi light brown, unmarked; antennae light brown with 
<number id="DE3960413D096226FBB6FA97FBA54C65" box="[1115,1143,1335,1360]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" value="59.0">59</number>
antennomeres covered by dark brown bristles, antennal fossa with a anterior black mark, scape 
<number id="DE3960413D096226FC73FAFCFC134C40" box="[926,961,1372,1397]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" value="1.5">1.5</number>
as high as wide, with lateral brown stripe.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="684E72663D096226FF2AFADFFBC54E35" blockId="1.[151,1437,1084,2009]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">
<emphasis id="5A85AE743D096226FF2AFADFFEF24CAD" bold="true" box="[199,288,1407,1432]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="F0CA6EE33D096226FEDFFADFFEA74CAD" box="[306,373,1407,1432]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1553,1575]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,198,1515]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,193,1516]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hemerobiella periotoi Sosa &amp; Lara sp. nov. female (Rio Claro “ Piedra del Tigre sector ” Lara state, Venezuela). A. Habitus. B. Head, frontal. C. Head and thorax, dorsal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/253673/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">
Fig. 
<number id="DE3960413D096226FE87FA20FEA74CAD" box="[362,373,1408,1432]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
C). Pronotum dark brown, longer than wide (length/smaller width: 
<number id="DE3960413D096226FB6BFA20FB7E4CAD" box="[1158,1196,1408,1432]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" value="1.7">1.7</number>
; length/larger width: 1.0), densely covered by long, light brown pilosity; mesoprescutum reddish brown medially, dark brown posteriorly; mesoscutum and metanotum dark brown dorsomedially, light brown laterally; pleural areas light brown, unmarked. Legs light brown, except for two dorsolateral rounded black spots on protibiae. 
<emphasis id="5A85AE743D096226FAFDFA4CFA894F30" bold="true" box="[1296,1371,1516,1541]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">Wings</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="F0CA6EE33D096226FA83FA4CFF704F1D" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1553,1575]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,198,1515]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,193,1516]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hemerobiella periotoi Sosa &amp; Lara sp. nov. female (Rio Claro “ Piedra del Tigre sector ” Lara state, Venezuela). A. Habitus. B. Head, frontal. C. Head and thorax, dorsal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/253673/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">
Fig. 
<number id="DE3960413D096226FF7AF9B0FF704F1D" box="[151,162,1552,1576]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A). Forewing length:10.0 mm, 
<number id="DE3960413D096226FDE4F9B0FDFE4F1D" box="[521,556,1552,1576]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" value="2.2">2.2</number>
times as long as wide; costal area wide (
<number id="DE3960413D096226FBE8F9B0FBFB4F1D" box="[1029,1065,1552,1576]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" value="0.3">0.3</number>
times width of wing). Forewing hyaline and densely marked by brown infuscations, venation with alternating dark and light brown coloration, 
<number id="DE3960413D096226FA98F994FA514F79" box="[1397,1411,1588,1612]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" value="2.0">2</number>
rm bordered by hyaline spot, second and third radial sector marked with circular black spot medially, humeral vein strongly recurrent, pterostigma with a light brown mark on Sc margin, three radial sectors originating in basal half of wing, radial veins distinctly sinuate in the distal portion, five outer and three inner gradates. Hindwing length: 
<quantity id="AF09DF833D096226FF7AF964FF204FE9" box="[151,242,1732,1756]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.8" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" unit="mm" value="7.8">7.8 mm</quantity>
, 
<number id="DE3960413D096226FEECF964FEF64FE9" box="[257,292,1732,1756]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" value="2.2">2.2</number>
times as long as wide; membrane hyaline, venation light brown, except with brown coloration on pterostigma and forked veins along all wings, four outer and one inner gradates.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="684E72663D096226FF2AF8ACFB404EEC" blockId="1.[151,1437,1084,2009]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">
<emphasis id="5A85AE743D096226FF2AF8ACFEEE4E10" bold="true" box="[199,316,1804,1829]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">Abdomen</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="5A85AE743D096226FEA4F8ACFE544E10" bold="true" box="[329,390,1804,1829]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">Male</emphasis>
: Unknown. 
<emphasis id="5A85AE743D096226FDFDF8ACFDB54E10" bold="true" box="[528,615,1804,1829]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">Female</emphasis>
. Brown, densely covered by dark brown pilosity. Ninth tergite elongated, narrow, with slight posteroventral digitiform projection extending below ectoproct (
<figureCitation id="F0CA6EE33D096226FBA3F88FFB414E7D" box="[1102,1171,1839,1864]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1821,1843]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,303,1755]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,303,1799]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hemerobiella periotoi Sosa &amp; Lara sp. nov. female (Rio Claro “ Piedra del Tigre sector ” Lara state, Venezuela). A. Apex of abdomen, lateral. B. Apex of abdomen, ventral. C. Gonapophysis lateralis, ventral and subgenital plate, ventral. D – E. Spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/253674/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">
Fig. 
<number id="DE3960413D096226FB69F890FB414E7D" box="[1156,1171,1840,1864]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
A). Ectoproct trapezoid in lateral view, projected posteroventrally, rounded apically, ventral margin ca. 
<number id="DE3960413D096226FBC3F8F4FBEE4E59" box="[1070,1084,1876,1900]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" value="2.0">2</number>
times the length of the dorsal margin (
<figureCitation id="F0CA6EE33D096226FF18F8D7FEEB4EA5" box="[245,313,1911,1936]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1821,1843]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,303,1755]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,303,1799]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hemerobiella periotoi Sosa &amp; Lara sp. nov. female (Rio Claro “ Piedra del Tigre sector ” Lara state, Venezuela). A. Apex of abdomen, lateral. B. Apex of abdomen, ventral. C. Gonapophysis lateralis, ventral and subgenital plate, ventral. D – E. Spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/253674/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">
Fig. 
<number id="DE3960413D096226FEC7F8D8FEEB4EA5" box="[298,313,1912,1936]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
A); callus cerci with 
<number id="DE3960413D096226FDC9F8D7FD924EA5" box="[548,576,1911,1936]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" value="16.0">16</number>
trichobothria. Gonapophysis lateralis ovoid (
<figureCitation id="F0CA6EE33D096226FBD0F8D7FB524EA5" box="[1085,1152,1911,1936]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1821,1843]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,303,1755]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,303,1799]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hemerobiella periotoi Sosa &amp; Lara sp. nov. female (Rio Claro “ Piedra del Tigre sector ” Lara state, Venezuela). A. Apex of abdomen, lateral. B. Apex of abdomen, ventral. C. Gonapophysis lateralis, ventral and subgenital plate, ventral. D – E. Spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/253674/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">
Fig. 
<number id="DE3960413D096226FB9FF8D8FB524EA5" box="[1138,1152,1912,1936]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
A–C). Spermathecal duct long, curved basally, straight towards apex; spermatheca cylindrical, roughened, curved on itself (
<figureCitation id="F0CA6EE33D096226FAFFF83CFA8A4E81" box="[1298,1368,1948,1973]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1821,1843]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,303,1755]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,303,1799]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hemerobiella periotoi Sosa &amp; Lara sp. nov. female (Rio Claro “ Piedra del Tigre sector ” Lara state, Venezuela). A. Apex of abdomen, lateral. B. Apex of abdomen, ventral. C. Gonapophysis lateralis, ventral and subgenital plate, ventral. D – E. Spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/253674/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">
Fig. 
<number id="DE3960413D096226FAA7F83CFA8A4E81" box="[1354,1368,1948,1972]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
D–E). Subgenital plate cordiform with coriaceous membrane (
<figureCitation id="F0CA6EE33D096226FCEAF860FC984EED" box="[775,842,1984,2009]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1821,1843]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,303,1755]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,303,1799]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hemerobiella periotoi Sosa &amp; Lara sp. nov. female (Rio Claro “ Piedra del Tigre sector ” Lara state, Venezuela). A. Apex of abdomen, lateral. B. Apex of abdomen, ventral. C. Gonapophysis lateralis, ventral and subgenital plate, ventral. D – E. Spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/253674/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">
Fig. 
<number id="DE3960413D096226FCD6F860FC984EED" box="[827,842,1984,2008]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
C); bursa copulatrix saccular.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="3C8E22EE3D0A6225FF7AF9B1FD694F73" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/253673/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="423" targetBox="[151,1436,198,1515]" targetPageId="2">
