<subSubSection id="20EB21ED3D0A6224FF2AF931FCB049CD" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="424" pageId="2" pageNumber="423" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="684E72663D0A6225FF2AF931FBEC4FC7" blockId="2.[151,1437,1645,2033]" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">
<emphasis id="5A85AE743D0A6225FF2AF931FE944F9F" bold="true" box="[199,326,1681,1706]" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">Etymology</emphasis>
. The name is aimed to honor the Brazilian entomologist Nelson Wanderley Perioto, who is dedicated to the study of the Brazilian 
<taxonomicName id="AFF109E53D0A6225FD84F915FD284FFB" box="[617,762,1717,1742]" class="Insecta" family="Eurytomidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="423" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Eurytomidae</taxonomicName>
(Insecta: 
<taxonomicName id="AFF109E53D0A6225FC9CF916FBDD4FFB" box="[881,1039,1718,1742]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="423" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Hymenoptera</taxonomicName>
); he is also a great friend and an enthusiastic collaborator in the study of the Brazilian Hemerobiids and Chrysopids.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="684E72663D0A6225FF2AF95DFCB54E23" blockId="2.[151,1437,1645,2033]" box="[199,871,1789,1814]" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">
<emphasis id="5A85AE743D0A6225FF2AF95DFE2F4E23" bold="true" box="[199,509,1789,1814]" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">Geographical distribution</emphasis>
. 
<collectingCountry id="10E632F63D0A6225FDE6F95DFDAC4E23" box="[523,638,1789,1814]" name="Venezuela" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
(Lara state) (
<figureCitation id="F0CA6EE33D0A6225FCF8F95DFC8B4E23" box="[789,857,1789,1814]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1296,1318]" captionTargetBox="[160,1419,205,1268]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[159,1427,195,1274]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Map of collecting localities of Venezuelan Hemerobiella. Lara state (1); Yaracuy state (2); Aragua state (3); Amazonas state (4)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/253679/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">
Fig. 
<number id="DE3960413D0A6225FCA4F95EFC8B4E23" box="[841,857,1790,1814]" pageId="2" pageNumber="423" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="684E72663D0A6225FF2AF881FB534EB0" blockId="2.[151,1437,1645,2033]" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">
<emphasis id="5A85AE743D0A6225FF2AF881FE544E0F" bold="true" box="[199,390,1825,1850]" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">Ecological notes</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName id="AFF109E53D0A6225FE78F881FD5C4E0C" box="[405,654,1825,1849]" class="Insecta" family="Hemerobiidae" genus="Hemerobiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="423" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="periotoi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="5A85AE743D0A6225FE78F881FD5C4E0C" box="[405,654,1825,1849]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">Hemerobiella periotoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="41B6130F3D0A6225FD79F881FD3F4E0C" box="[660,749,1825,1850]" pageId="2" pageNumber="423" rank="species">
<emphasis id="5A85AE743D0A6225FD79F881FD7C4E0F" bold="true" box="[660,686,1825,1850]" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">sp</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="5A85AE743D0A6225FD51F881FD344E0F" bold="true" box="[700,742,1825,1850]" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
was collected in the shrubbery of mature cloud forest in Lara state near border of Terepaima National Park (
<figureCitation id="F0CA6EE33D0A6225FD40F8E5FD214E6B" box="[685,755,1861,1886]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,691,713]" captionTargetBox="[155,1433,194,669]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[150,1436,193,669]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Type locality. A. Piedra del Tigre sector (Rio Claro, Lara state, Venezuela), arrow indicating gateway to forest and shrubbery. B. Perspective of the shrubbery, arrows indicating the plants sampled." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/253675/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">
Fig. 
<number id="DE3960413D0A6225FD0EF8E6FD214E6B" box="[739,755,1862,1886]" pageId="2" pageNumber="423" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
). The area has elevation of 
<quantity id="AF09DF833D0A6225FBDBF8E5FB5C4E68" box="[1078,1166,1861,1886]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.425" pageId="2" pageNumber="423" unit="m" value="1425.0">1425 m</quantity>
about sea level, annual temperatures and precipitation ranging between 
<number id="DE3960413D0A6225FD5EF8CCFD2B4EB0" box="[691,761,1900,1925]" pageId="2" pageNumber="423" value="22.5" valueMax="26.0" valueMin="19.0">19–26</number>
o C and 
<quantity id="AF09DF833D0A6225FCA7F8CDFC3F4EB1" box="[842,1005,1901,1925]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="2" pageNumber="423" unit="mm" value="1400.0" valueMax="2000.0" valueMin="800.0">800–2000 mm</quantity>
respectively.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="684E72663D0A6224FF2AF830FCB049CD" blockId="2.[151,1437,1645,2033]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1437,151,248]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="424" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">
<emphasis id="5A85AE743D0A6225FF2AF830FE784E9C" bold="true" box="[199,426,1936,1961]" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">Comparative notes</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="AFF109E53D0A6225FE57F830FD664E9D" box="[442,692,1936,1960]" class="Insecta" family="Hemerobiidae" genus="Hemerobiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="423" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="periotoi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="5A85AE743D0A6225FE57F830FD664E9D" box="[442,692,1936,1960]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">Hemerobiella periotoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="41B6130F3D0A6225FD51F830FCC54E9D" box="[700,791,1936,1961]" pageId="2" pageNumber="423" rank="species">
<emphasis id="5A85AE743D0A6225FD51F830FD044E9C" bold="true" box="[700,726,1936,1961]" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">sp</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="5A85AE743D0A6225FD0BF830FCC24E9C" bold="true" box="[742,784,1936,1961]" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be separated from 
<taxonomicName id="AFF109E53D0A6225FBCEF831FB4A4E9D" box="[1059,1176,1937,1960]" class="Insecta" family="Hemerobiidae" genus="Hemerobiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="423" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinuata">
<emphasis id="5A85AE743D0A6225FBCEF831FBE54E9D" box="[1059,1079,1937,1960]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="5A85AE743D0A6225FBABF831FB4A4E9D" box="[1094,1176,1937,1960]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">sinuata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="AFF109E53D0A6225FB3FF831FA9F4E9D" box="[1234,1357,1936,1960]" class="Insecta" family="Hemerobiidae" genus="Hemerobiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="423" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oswaldi">
<emphasis id="5A85AE743D0A6225FB3FF831FB344E9D" box="[1234,1254,1937,1960]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="5A85AE743D0A6225FB1BF830FA9F4E9D" box="[1270,1357,1936,1960]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">oswaldi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the large black, mesal mark between the second and third radial sector on the forewing (
<figureCitation id="F0CA6EE33D0A6225FB99F814FB674EF8" box="[1140,1205,1972,1997]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1553,1575]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,198,1515]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,193,1516]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hemerobiella periotoi Sosa &amp; Lara sp. nov. female (Rio Claro “ Piedra del Tigre sector ” Lara state, Venezuela). A. Habitus. B. Head, frontal. C. Head and thorax, dorsal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/253673/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">
Fig. 
<number id="DE3960413D0A6225FB46F815FB674EF8" box="[1195,1205,1973,1997]" pageId="2" pageNumber="423" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A) and female with subgenital plate cordiform bearing coriaceous membrane (
<figureCitation id="F0CA6EE33D0A6225FCD4F878FC524EC4" box="[825,896,2008,2033]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1821,1843]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,303,1755]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,303,1799]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hemerobiella periotoi Sosa &amp; Lara sp. nov. female (Rio Claro “ Piedra del Tigre sector ” Lara state, Venezuela). A. Apex of abdomen, lateral. B. Apex of abdomen, ventral. C. Gonapophysis lateralis, ventral and subgenital plate, ventral. D – E. Spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/253674/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">
Fig. 
<number id="DE3960413D0A6225FC9CF879FC524EC4" box="[881,896,2009,2033]" pageId="2" pageNumber="423" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
C). However, 
<emphasis id="5A85AE743D0A6225FBCEF879FA844EC5" box="[1059,1366,2008,2032]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">
<taxonomicName id="AFF109E53D0A6225FBCEF879FB494EC5" box="[1059,1179,2009,2032]" class="Insecta" family="Hemerobiidae" genus="Hemerobiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="423" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinuata">H. sinuata</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="AFF109E53D0A6225FB34F879FA844EC5" box="[1241,1366,2008,2032]" class="Insecta" family="Hemerobiidae" genus="Hemerobiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="423" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oswaldi">H. oswaldi</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
share external features and these species significantly differ in the shape of female subgenital plate, being granulate, with a U-shaped incision and two tenuous laminar pieces in 
<taxonomicName id="AFF109E53D0B6224FCD8FF1DFBAC49E1" authority="Kimmins 1940" authorityName="Kimmins" authorityYear="1940" box="[821,1150,188,213]" class="Insecta" family="Hemerobiidae" genus="Hemerobiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="424" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinuata">
<emphasis id="5A85AE743D0B6224FCD8FF1DFC9B49E1" box="[821,841,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="424">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="5A85AE743D0B6224FCB0FF1DFC7D49E1" box="[861,943,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="424">sinuata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="0C600F973D0B6224FC29FF1CFBA549E1" author="Kimmins" box="[964,1143,188,213]" pageId="3" pageNumber="424" refString="Kimmins, D. E. (1940) New genera and species of Hemerobiidae (Neuroptera). Annals and Magazine of Natural History, 11 (6), 222 - 236. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222934008527092" type="journal article" year="1940">
Kimmins 
<number id="DE3960413D0B6224FBD6FF1CFBA549E1" box="[1083,1143,188,212]" pageId="3" pageNumber="424" value="1940.0">1940</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, while in 
<taxonomicName id="AFF109E53D0B6224FB10FF1DFAAE49E1" box="[1277,1404,188,212]" class="Insecta" family="Hemerobiidae" genus="Hemerobiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="424" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oswaldi">
<emphasis id="5A85AE743D0B6224FB10FF1DFAAE49E1" box="[1277,1404,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="424">H. oswaldi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is spherical, with a U-shaped incision (
<figureCitation id="F0CA6EE33D0B6224FDDDFF7FFDA149CD" box="[560,627,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1310,1332]" captionTargetBox="[157,1431,199,1283]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,193,1289]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Hemerobiella oswaldi Monserrat, 1998 (Henri Pittier National Park, Aragua state, Venezuela) .. Female terminalia. A. Apex of abdomen, lateral. B. Apex of abdomen, ventral. C. Gonapophysis lateralis and subgenital plate, ventral. D. Spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/253678/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="424">
Fig. 
<number id="DE3960413D0B6224FD88FF7FFDA149CD" box="[613,627,223,248]" pageId="3" pageNumber="424" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
C) (
<bibRefCitation id="0C600F973D0B6224FD70FF40FC8749CD" author="Monserrat" box="[669,853,224,248]" pageId="3" pageNumber="424" refString="Monserrat, V. J. (1998) Nuevos datos sobre los hemerobidos de America (Neuroptera: Hemerobiidae). Journal of Neuropterology, 1, 109 - 153." type="journal article" year="1998">
<collectingCountry id="10E632F63D0B6224FD70FF40FCC049CD" box="[669,786,224,248]" name="Montserrat" pageId="3" pageNumber="424">Monserrat</collectingCountry>
<number id="DE3960413D0B6224FCF4FF40FC8749CD" box="[793,853,224,248]" pageId="3" pageNumber="424" value="1998.0">1998</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
